  "steps": [
    "Clean nanodrop by adding 1ul MilliQ, closing and wiping off with Kim Wipe undetermined MilliQ water Contributed by users",
    "Open nanodrop program. Click Nucleic Acid, then DNA.",
    "Activate machine by adding 1ul MilliQ water, closing machine and clicking OK. Wipe off gently with Kim Wipe.",
    "Blank machine by adding 1ul of the buffer that the DNA was eluted with (ie TE). Close machine and click measure blank. Wipe off gently with Kim Wipe.",
    "To measure sample, add 1ul of sample to nanodrop, close machine and click Measure. Wipe off gently with Kim Wipe. Repeat for all samples."
